# Star Citizen Data Sources

When needing Star Citizen game data (components, shops, mining, ships, etc.), check these sources **first** before web searching:

## Primary Data Sources

### 1. UEX Corp API (Live Shop Data)
**URL:** https://uexcorp.space/api/documentation

Crowdsourced live game data for all systems (Stanton, Pyro, Nyx). Key endpoints:
- `/terminals` - All shop/terminal locations with system info
- `/items_prices_all` - All items and prices across all terminals
- `/items_prices` - Specific item/terminal prices
- No auth required for read endpoints
- Updated hourly by community reporters
- **Use for:** Shop inventories, prices, locations (all systems)

### 2. richardthombs/scunpacked (Static Game Data)
**URL:** https://github.com/richardthombs/scunpacked

⚠️ **Note:** This repo is archived and only has Stanton data. Use UEX for shop data.

Game data extracted from Star Citizen files. Key files in `api/dist/json/`:
- `items.json` - All game items (~15MB)
- `ship-items.json` - Ship equipment index
- `ships.json` - Ship data
- `manufacturers.json` - Manufacturer info
- `starmap.json` - Location data
- `shops.json` - ⚠️ OUTDATED (Stanton only, no Pyro/Nyx)

### 3. seneca0815-rgb/SC_Signature_Scanner
**URL:** https://github.com/seneca0815-rgb/SC_Signature_Scanner

Mining RS signature data:
- `lookup.json` - 163 signature values for 26 minerals × 6 multipliers

### 4. MrKraken/StarStrings
**URL:** https://github.com/MrKraken/StarStrings

Component and ordnance localization data for Star Citizen:
- `components.ini` - Component types, grades, manufacturers, display names
- `ordnance.ini` - Missiles and torpedoes
- `mining.ini` - Mining ore locations and rarity
- `contracts.ini` - Contract blueprint pools

## Usage Pattern

1. Identify what data is needed
2. **Shop/price data:** Use UEX Corp API (has all systems including Pyro/Nyx)
3. **Static game data:** Check scunpacked for items, ships, etc.
4. **Component names/categorization:** Check StarStrings
5. **Mining signatures:** Check SC_Signature_Scanner
6. Only web search if none of these sources have the data

## Notes

- UEX provides live, community-sourced data for all game systems
- scunpacked is archived and only has Stanton shop data
- StarStrings provides curated display names and categorization
- Hand-mineable gems share base RS 620 (not useful for identification)
- Ship-mineable ores each have unique signatures (3170-4300 range)
